post_text:
Parents,

Thank you for your questions and concerns over the family commitment survey. As we work to develop a plan for the DOH this information will be very important. I understand you wanting to make an informed decision so please look for communication on Monday that will provide more details on what school will look like whether we are in person or remote. I have received numerous emails from you and we are monitoring Facebook as well so we will do our best to address all your concerns and questions. Your communication has been very respectful of the situation we are faced with and that is greatly appreciated.

Have a great day,

Mike Nollan, Superintendent

Kittitas School District

509-955-3121

mike_nollan@ksd403.org

post_text: Don't forget, the Kittitas SD surplus sale is happening today! Doors close at 3pm.
text: Don't forget, the Kittitas SD surplus sale is happening today! Doors close at 3pm.

post_text:
Reminder about our public surplus sale Tuesday, June 30th from 7am - 3pm. The sale will be held in the Jimmy Johnson Memorial Gym. Only cash and checks will be accepted.

Please review the following guidelines that will be in place for this event:

1. Face-coverings (any cloth that covers both the nose and mouth) are required for entry into the sale. NO EXCEPTIONS!
2. Hand sanitizer will be available.
3. 10-15 people (including those working the event) will be allowed inside the gym at one time.
4. One doorway will be designated for entering the sale and a separate doorway will be used for exiting. The entrance will be at the east end of the building along Pierce St.
5. Six foot spacing will be marked on the pavement outside the entrance in the event that a line forms.

Please contact the district office at 855-380-8844 if you have additional questions.

Thank you for your cooperation!

post_text: Congratulations Wyatt Crowley!! Wyatt Crowley, Amelia Haller (Selah), and Evin Harvey (Naches) represented Washington as members of the District 5 West Valley WAHSET team at the Pacific Northwest Invitational Challenge (PNWIC) in Team Penning competition in Redmond, OR. Wyatt, Amelia, and Evin earned the 1st place award by penning 9 head of cattle in a total time of 125.75 seconds. The 2nd place team penned 7 head in total time of 183.09 seconds. This the second straight year Wyatt and Amelia have won the PNWIC in team penning/sorting. PNWIC pits the top 5 competitors from the Oregon High School Equestrian Team State Championship against the top 5 competitors from the Washington High School Equestrian Team State Championship.

post_text:
Update on Superintendent search:

The application period for the Kittitas Superintendent ended January 3, 2019. According to our superintendent search consultant, Rich Parker, there are 27 completed applications. The next step is for our search consultant to check on all the references and background of each candidate and bring a list of recommendations to our school board. The Kittitas School Board will meet in executive session on January 29th to review all the applicants and the recommended list from our consultant. The board will select five to six candidates to interview as semi-finalists and then select three to visit our district for all day interviews.

shared_text:
Family, Career and Community Leaders of America
October 15, 2018 at 5:46 AM ·

Celebrate Global Handwashing 2018 with FCCLA as we recognize Kittitas Secondary School FCCLA, for earning the 2018 Healthy Schools, Healthy People, It’s a SNAP national award, sponsored by the American Cleaning Institute.

State Officer, Grace Allphin said that "peer educating the Kittitas elementary students on how to properly wash their hands was an experience I will never forget. Using our mascot Paws was the ticket to getting the attention of the kids. The impact of our project was all positive, absenteeism was reduced, our community became more aware of our organization and we earned the trip of a lifetime to Washington DC."

https://www.cleaninginstitute.org/healthy_schools_healthy_people/

American Cleaning Institute CDC Global Handwashing Day

Kittitas Fastpitch is headed back to state for the 12th year in a row. They won the EWAC League title and EWAC Tourney title, as well as took 2nd place in the D5/D6 Tournament. We play Lind-Ritzville/Sprague/Wastucna at 9 am tomorrow in the opening round of state and if we win, we'll play tomorrow evening at 7 pm against either Adna or Dayton/Waitsburg.

Academically, our overall team GPA is 3.58, which was recognized by the WIAA as "Outstanding."

Our state’s lead office for education – the Office of Superintendent of Public Instruction (OSPI), led by State Superintendent Chris Reykdal – just opened a survey to the public asking for input on public K-12 education investments for the future. This is the first time families, educators, students, and community members will have an opportunity to give input about the areas where state leaders should focus funding.

I hope you will be able to take five minutes to make your voice heard and be part of the conversation at the statewide level.

We need volunteers! Help team-teach Computer Science at Kittitas Secondary school

TEALS places volunteer CS experts with local high school teachers looking to make a lasting impact on their students’ lives. Next year TEALS will partner volunteers with our computer science teacher at Kittitas Secondary school to offer an Introduction to Computer Science class. Help shape the future in our community by applying your computer science skills in the classroom a few hours a week. Learn more at tealsk12.org/volunteers.

We are very excited about our upcoming Senior Citizen Prom that middle school students are putting on for our community! They have had a blast researching the past and coming up with fun ideas to make this a memorable event.

We are reaching out to you to see if you would be interested in donating to our awesome event. Students plan to serve dessert and drinks, crown a King and Queen, play music from the 50s and 60s, have a yearbook table and much more.

If you feel like you or your business could donate to this event please contact Jaime Smith, Leadership Advisor at 855-380-8848 or donations can be dropped off at the school.

Thank you for your consideration!

post_text: Attention all Kittitas High School alumni baseball/softball players. We are putting together a four inning softball game next Thursday, April 5th, beginning at 6:00 pm, in an effort to raise money for NF1. This is a disease that affected one of our very own Coyotes, David Eilers. We are honoring David all next week, and since he was the water boy/assistant coach for both the football and baseball teams, we thought that an alumni softball game would be very fitting. If you or someone you know would like to be a part of this special tribute to David, please PM me and let me know!! The more participants, the more fun it will be!! Thank you in advance! 💙⚾🎗️

UPDATE ON TONIGHT'S AWAY BASKETBALL GAMES:
Bad news from some bad luck. Our first bus today had some mechanical problems and had to return to Kittitas and reload onto a different bus. They will not arrive on time to play all games as scheduled.

TCP made the decision to cancel the girls JV due to it only being two quarters and try to play as much of the boys JV game as allowed. Once the team arrives an end time will be set for the boys JV game to start the girls varsity as scheduled. There will be a period of running clock most likely at the end of the boys JV to accommodate this.

Sorry for any inconvenience this may cause. Players on the bus have been instructed to notify parents/fans if they are able.

post_text:
MESSAGE FROM SUPERINTENDENT RICH STEWART

Dear Parents, Guardians and Community,

First, I want to thank all of you for your patience as we go through this smoke-filled time period. As your superintendent it is important that the safety of our students is assured. When I made the decision to close our schools, the air quality inside our schools was above safe levels. Since that time the air quality outside has improved to moderate levels. However, we want to make sure that the indoor quality is safe as well. We are contracting with a local company to monitor and help us with necessary changes we might make. I feel very confident that we will get to start school on Monday, but please watch for any changes on Sunday evening. As always, we are using Facebook and our website to share important information.

Thank you for your support and we are looking forward to seeing all the kids on Monday.
text:
MESSAGE FROM SUPERINTENDENT RICH STEWART

Dear Parents, Guardians and Community,

First, I want to thank all of you for your patience as we go through this smoke-filled time period. As your superintendent it is important that the safety of our students is assured. When I made the decision to close our schools, the air quality inside our schools was above safe levels. Since that time the air quality outside has improved to moderate levels. However, we want to make sure that the indoor quality is safe as well. We are contracting with a local company to monitor and help us with necessary changes we might make. I feel very confident that we will get to start school on Monday, but please watch for any changes on Sunday evening. As always, we are using Facebook and our website to share important information.

Thank you for your support and we are looking forward to seeing all the kids on Monday.

post_text:
From Kittitas Secondary School:
Today our teachers had conversations with your children about "What is Peer Conflict, Mean Behavior and Bullying?" They watched a video and completed a worksheet to ensure students understood the differences and harm each behavior can cause.
Please take some time to discuss with them what those differences are, what they learned and what each student can do to help promote a safe environment at school and on social media.
- Del Heistand, Principal

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iiGjbm1BI6k&feature=youtu.be

post_text:
On April 5 at 6:30pm, the Board of Directors will begin the process of reviewing the current status of the KSD facilities as the first step in considering any future renovations. The community is invited to attend this meeting. Be prepared to join us for a short tour and discussions focused on the conditions and challenges that face the district. The meeting will begin in the board room in the District Office.

If you have questions, please contact Superintendent Mike Messenger at mike_messenger@ksd403.org or 855-380-8844.

post_text:
"Late-Start" Town Hall Meetings:
The District is considering a "one-hour late start" schedule on Mondays for the 2017-2018 school year. You are invited to one of the meetings to learn more about the proposal and share your thoughts.

Auvil Fruit - April 5, 4:00pm
Kittitas Secondary - April 12, 6:30pm
Kittitas Elementary - April 13, 6:30pm

If you have questions, please contact Superintendent Mike Messenger at mike_messenger@ksd403.org or 855-380-8844.
